 the Hands of the Viewer: on art and activism</title><link href="https://www.majalorkowska.com/2021/07/29/all-in-the-hands-of-the-viewer-on-art-and-activism.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="All in the Hands of the Viewer: on art and activism" /><published>2021-07-29T17:40:00+01:00</published><updated>2021-07-29T17:40:00+01:00</updated><id>https://www.majalorkowska.com/2021/07/29/all-in-the-hands-of-the-viewer-on-art-and-activism</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://www.majalorkowska.com/2021/07/29/all-in-the-hands-of-the-viewer-on-art-and-activism.html">&lt;p&gt;Before members of the UN summit in 2003 sat down to debate whether or not to engage in a war against Iraq, the tapestry reproduction of ‘Guernica’, which was usually the backdrop to events held in the building, was covered up. While the gesture was dismissed as a practical necessity, it still perfectly illustrates that Picasso’s activist gesture continues to hold power 80 years later.&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html">Before members of the UN summit in 2003 sat down to debate whether or not to engage in a war against Iraq, the tapestry reproduction of ‘Guernica’, which was usually the backdrop to events held in the building, was covered up. While the gesture was dismissed as a practical necessity, it still perfectly illustrates that Picasso’s activist gesture continues to hold power 80 years later.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.majalorkowska.com/assets/uploads/cl1.png" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://www.majalorkowska.com/assets/uploads/cl1.png" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Drop II</title><link href="https://www.majalorkowska.com/collage/2021/07/29/drop-ii.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Drop II" /><published>2021-07-29T08:55:16+01:00</published><updated>2021-07-29T08:55:16+01:00</updated><id>https://www.majalorkowska.com